obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (33225)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33225&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Expenditure-tax`
  line `Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st November, 1987, vide notification No. S.O. 919(E), dated 14th October, 1987, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (33226)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 114 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33226&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "assessee" means a person responsible for collecting the expenditure-tax payable under the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(2) "assessment year" means the period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April`
  line `every year;`
  line
  line `(3) "Board" means the Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963);`
  line
  line `(4) "chargeable expenditure" means the expenditure referred to in section 5;`
  line
  line `(5) "expenditure-tax" or "tax" means the tax chargeable under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(6) "hotel" includes a building or part of a building where residential accommodation is, by way`
  line `of business, provided for a monetary consideration;`
  line
  line `(7) "Income-tax Act" means the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(8) "person responsible for collecting" means a person who is required to collect tax under this`
  line `Act or is required to pay any other sum of money under this Act and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) every person in respect of whom any proceedings under this Act have been taken, and`
  line
  line `(b) every person who is deemed to be an assessee-in-default under any provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(9) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(9A) "restaurant" means any premises, not being a restaurant situated in a hotel referred to in`
  line `clause (1) of section 3, in which the business of sale of food or drink to the public is carried on and`
  line `such premises, at the beginning of any month, are equipped with, or have access to, facilities for`
  line air-conditioning;]
  line
  line `(10) "room charges" means the charges for a unit of residential accommodation in a hotel and`
  line `includes the charges for--`
  line
  line `(a) furniture, air-conditioner, refrigerator, radio, music, telephone, television, and`
  line
  line `(b) such other services as are normally included by a hotel in room rent,`
  line
  line `but does not include charges for food, drinks and any services other than those referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses (a) and (b);`
  line
  line `(11) all other words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Income-tax`
  line `Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (33227)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33227&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[3. Application of the Act.--This Act shall apply in relation to any chargeable expenditure--`
  line
  line `(1) ^2`
  line `[incurred before the 1st day of June, 2003 in a hotel] wherein the room charges for any unit`
  line `of residential accommodation at the time of incurring of such expenditure are ^3`
  line `[three thousand rupees`
  line `or more per day] and where,--`
  line
  line `(a) a composite charge is payable in respect of such unit and food, the room charges included`
  line `therein shall be determined in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(b) (i) a composite charge is payable in respect of such unit, food, drinks and other services,`
  line `or any of them, and the case is not covered by the provisions of sub-clause (a), or`
  line
  line `(ii) it appears to the Assessing Officer that the charges for such unit, food, drinks or other`
  line `services are so arranged that the room charges are understated and the other charges are`
  line overstated,
  line
  line `the Assessing Officer shall, for the purposes of this clause determine the room charges on such reasonable`
  line `basis as he may deem fit; and`
  line `(2) incurred in a restaurant ^4`
  line `[before the 1st day of June, 1992.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 115, for sections 3 to 5 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 102, for "incurred in a hotel" (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 115, for "two thousand rupees or more per day per individual" (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 105 (w.e.f 1-6-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (33228)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Charge of expenditure-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33228&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, there shall be charged on and`
  line from--
  line
  line `(a) the commencement of this Act ^1`
  line `[but not after the 31st day of May, 2003], a tax at the rate of`
  line ^2
  line `[ten per cent.] of the chargeable expenditure incurred in a hotel referred to in clause (1) of section 3:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this clause shall apply in the case of a hotel referred to in ^3`
  line `[clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 80-IB] of the Income-tax Act during the period beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1991 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2001:`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[Provided further that nothing in this clause shall apply in the case of a hotel referred to in`
  line ^5
  line `[clause (a) of sub-section (7) of section 80-IB of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) during the`
  line `period beginning on the 1st day of April, 1998 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2008.]`
  line
  line `(b) the 1st day of October, 1991, ^6[but not after the 31st day of May, 1992] a tax at the rate of`
  line `fifteen per cent. of the chargeable expenditure incurred in a restaurant referred to in clause (2) of`
  line `section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 103 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 57, for "twenty per cent." (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 98, for "clause (ii) of sub-section (5) of section 80-IA" (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by 27 of 1999, s. 98, for "clause (iia) or sub-section (5) of section 80-1A" (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 106, for "the commencement of this Act" (w.e.f. 1-6-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (33229)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Meaning of chargeable expenditure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33229&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, chargeable expenditure,--`
  line
  line `(1) in relation to a hotel referred to in clause (1) of section 3, means any expenditure incurred in,`
  line `or payments made to, the hotel in connection with the provision of--`
  line
  line `(a) any accommodation, residential or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) any accommodation in such hotel on hire or lease; or`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `but does not include--`
  line
  line `(i) any expenditure which is incurred, or payment for which is made, in foreign exchange`
  line `^3[before the 1st day of October, 1992;]`
  line
  line `(ii) any expenditure incurred by persons within the purview of the Vienna Convention on`
  line `Diplomatic Relations, 1961 or the Vienna Convention on Consular Relations, 1963;`
  line
  line `(iii) any expenditure incurred in any shop or in any office which is not owned or managed`
  line `by the person who carries on the business of a hotel;`
  line
  line `(iv) any expenditure by way of any tax, including tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause,--`
  line
  line `(a) expenditure incurred or any payments made in Indian currency obtained by`
  line `conversion of foreign exchange into Indian currency shall in such cases and in such`
  line `circumstances as may be prescribed be deemed to have been incurred or, as the case may be,`
  line `made in foreign exchange; and`
  line
  line `(b) "foreign exchange" and "Indian currency" shall have the meanings respectively`
  line `assigned to them in clauses (h) and (k) of section 2 of the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act,`
  line `1973 (46 of 1973);`
  line
  line `(2) in relation to a restaurant referred to in clause (2) of section 3, means any expenditure incurred`
  line `in, or payments made to, a restaurant in connection with the provision of food or drink by the`
  line `restaurant, whether at the restaurant or outside, or by any other person in the restaurant, but does not`
  line `include any expenditure referred to in sub-clauses (ii) and (iv) of clause (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-clause (b) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 116 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-clause (d) omitted by s. 116, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 107 (w.e.f. 1-6-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (33230)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Tax authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33230&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Every Director General of Income-tax, Chief Commissioner of Income-tax,`
  line `tax, Director of Income-tax, Commissioner of Income-tax, Commissioner of Income-tax`
  line `(Appeals) ^2`
  line `[Additional Director of Income-tax, ^3`
  line `[Joint Director of Income-tax, Joint Commissioner of`
  line `Income-tax] Deputy Director] of Income tax, Deputy Commissioner of Income-tax, Assistant Director`
  line `Income-tax, Assistant Commissioner of Income-tax, Income-tax Officer, Tax Recovery Officer and`
  line `Inspector of Income-tax shall have the like powers and perform the like functions under this Act as he has`
  line `and performs under the Income-tax Act, and for the exercise of his powers and the performance of his`
  line `functions, his jurisdiction under this Act shall be the same as he has under the Income-tax Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) All officers and persons employed in the execution of this Act shall observe and follow the orders,`
  line `instructions and directions of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued--`
  line
  line `(a) so as to require any tax authority to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a`
  line `particular case in a particular manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) so as to interfere with the discretion of the ^4`
  line `[Chief Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `(Appeals) in the exercise of his appellate functions.`
  line
  line `(3) Every ^5`
  line `[Assessing Officer] employed in the execution of this Act shall observe and follow the`
  line `the orders, instructions and directions issued for his guidance by the ^6`
  line `[Director General or Director or`
  line `by the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] or by the ^7`
  line `[Additional Commissioner of Income-tax`
  line `or] ^8`
  line `[Joint Commissioner] within whose jurisdiction he performs his functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 73, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 58, for "Deputy Director" (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 82, for "Additional Commissioner of Income-Tax" (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by, s. 72, ibid., for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 73, for "Director of Inspection or by the Commissioner" (w.e.f 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 58, for "Deputy Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 82, for "Deputy Commissioner" (w.e.f 1-10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (33231)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Collection and recovery of expenditure-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33231&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[7. Collection and recovery of expenditure-tax.--(1) Where any chargeable expenditure is`
  line `incurred in a hotel referred to in clause (1) of section 3,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such expenditure relates to any of the services, specified in sub-clauses (a) to (d) of`
  line `clause (1) of section 5, provided by the hotel, the person who carries on the business of such hotel;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) if such expenditure relates to any of the services, specified in sub-clause (b) or sub-clause (d)`
  line `of clause (1) of section 5, provided by the other person referred to therein, such other person,`
  line
  line `shall collect the expenditure-tax at the rate specified in clause (a) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any chargeable expenditure is incurred in a restaurant referred to in clause (2) of section 3`
  line ^2
  line `[before the 1st day of June, 1992] in relation to any services specified in clause (2) of section 5 and`
  line `where such services are--`
  line
  line `(a) provided by the restaurant, the person who carries on the business of such restaurant; and`
  line
  line `(b) provided by the other person, such other person,`
  line
  line `shall collect the expenditure-tax at the rate specified in clause (b) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(3) The tax collected during any calendar month in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be paid to the credit of the Central Government by the 10th of the month`
  line `immediately following the said calendar month.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person responsible for collecting the tax, who fails to collect the tax in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall, notwithstanding such failure, be liable to pay the tax`
  line `to the credit of the Central Government in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 116, for section 7 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 108 (w.e.f. 1-6-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (33232)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Person responsible for collecting tax to furnish prescribed return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33232&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person`
  line `responsible for collecting the tax shall before the expiry of four months from the 31st day of March in`
  line `each year, furnish or cause to be furnished to the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] in the prescribed form and verified`
  line `in the prescribed manner, a return in respect of the immediately preceding financial year showing--`
  line
  line `(a) the aggregate of the payments received in respect of chargeable expenditure;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of the tax collected;`
  line
  line `(c) the amount of the tax paid to the credit of the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any person who, in the opinion of the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer], is responsible for`
  line `collecting tax under this Act and who has not furnished a return under sub-section (1), the ^1`
  line [Assessing
  line `Officer] may, before the expiry of the financial year in which the return is to be furnished, issue a notice`
  line `to him and serve the same upon him, requiring him to furnish within thirty days from the date of service`
  line `of the notice the return in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner setting forth such`
  line `other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person responsible for collecting the tax who has not furnished the return within the time`
  line `allowed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), or having furnished a return under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) discovers any omission or wrong statement therein, may furnish a return or a revised`
  line `return, as the case may be, at any time before the assessment is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (33233)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33233&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of making an assessment under this Act, the ^1`
  line [Assessing
  line `Officer] may serve on any person who has furnished a return under section 8 or upon whom a notice has`
  line `been served under sub-section (2) of section 8 (whether a return has been furnished or not) a notice`
  line `requiring him on a date therein to be specified, to produce or cause to be produced such accounts or`
  line `documents or other evidence as the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] may require for the purposes of this Act and`
  line `may, from time to time, serve further notices requiring the production of such further accounts or`
  line `documents or other evidence as he may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer], after considering such accounts, documents or other evidence, if any, as`
  line `he has obtained under sub-section (1) and after taking into account any relevant material which he has`
  line `gathered, shall, by an order in writing, assess the chargeable expenditure and the amount of tax payable`
  line `on the basis of such assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (33234)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Best judgment assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33234&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line If--
  line
  line `(a) any person fails to make the return required by any notice given under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8 and has not made a return or a revised return under sub-section (3) of that section, or`
  line
  line `(b) any person having made a return fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9, or`
  line
  line `(c) the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] is not satisfied with the correctness or the completeness of the`
  line `accounts of the assessee,`
  line
  line `the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer], after taking into account all the relevant material which he has gathered, shall,`
  line `by an order in writing, make the assessment of the chargeable expenditure to the best of his judgment and`
  line `determine the sum payable by the assessee or refundable to the assessee on the basis of such assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (33235)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Chargeable expenditure escaping assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33235&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line If--
  line
  line `(a) the^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] has reason to believe that by reason of omission or failure on the part`
  line `of the assessee to make a return under section 8 for any assessment year or to disclose wholly and`
  line `truly all material facts necessary for his assessment for any assessment year, chargeable expenditure`
  line `for that year has escaped assessment or has been under-assessed, or`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding that there has been no omission or failure as mentioned in clause (a) on the`
  line `part of the assessee, the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] has, in consequence of information in his possession,`
  line `reason to believe that chargeable expenditure assessable in any assessment year has escaped`
  line `assessment or has been under-assessed,`
  line
  line `he may, in cases falling under clause (a), at any time, and in cases falling under clause (b), at any time`
  line `within four years from the end of that assessment year, serve on the assessee a notice containing all or any`
  line `of the requirements which may be included in a notice under section 8 and may proceed to assess or`
  line `reassess the chargeable expenditure, and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply, as if the`
  line `notice was a notice issued under that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (33236)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Rectification of mistake.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33236&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record,`
  line `the tax authority referred to in section 6 which passed any order under the provisions of this Act may,`
  line `within four years of the date on which such order was passed, amend the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any matter has been considered and decided in any proceeding by way of appeal or`
  line `revision relating to an order referred to in sub-section (1), the authority passing such order may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, amend the order under that`
  line `sub-section in relation to any matter other than the matter which has been so considered and decided.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the other provisions of this section, the authority concerned--`
  line
  line `(a) may make an amendment under sub-section (1) of its own motion, and`
  line
  line `(b) shall make such amendment if any mistake is brought to its notice,--`
  line
  line `(i) by the assessee; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the authority concerned is the ^2`
  line `[Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] (Appeals),`
  line `by the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer].`
  line
  line `(4) An amendment, which has the effect of enhancing an assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee, shall not be made under this section unless the authority`
  line `concerned has given notice to the assessee of its intention so to do and has allowed the assessee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an amendment is made under this section, an order shall be passed in writing by the tax`
  line `authority concerned.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, where any such amendment has the effect of reducing`
  line `the assessment, the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] shall make any refund which may be due to such assessee.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any such amendment has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing the refund`
  line `already made, the ^3`
  line `[Assessing Officer] shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed`
  line `form specifying the sum payable and such notice of demand shall be deemed to be issued under`
  line `section 20 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for "Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (33237)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Time limit for completion of assessment and reassessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33237&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No order of assessment shall`
  line `be made under section 9 or section 10 at any time after the expiration of a period of four years from the`
  line `end of the assessment year in which the chargeable expenditure was first assessable, or one year from the`
  line `date of the filing of the return or revised return under section 8, whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(2) No order of assessment or reassessment shall be made under section 11,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the assessment or reassessment is to be made in a case falling within clause (a) of`
  line `section 11 for which a notice has been served upon the assessee, at any time after the expiration of a`
  line `period of four years from the end of the assessment year in which the said notice was served;`
  line
  line `(b) where the assessment or reassessment is to be made in a case falling within clause (b) of`
  line `section 11, for which a notice has been served, after the expiration of a period of--`
  line
  line `(i) four years from the end of the assessment year in which the chargeable expenditure was`
  line `first assessable, or`
  line
  line `(ii) one year from the date of service of such notice,`
  line
  line `whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), an order of fresh assessment in`
  line `pursuance of an order passed under section 21, section 22 or section 23, setting aside or cancelling an`
  line `assessment, may be made at any time before the expiry of four years from the end of the financial year in`
  line `which the order under section 21 is passed by ^1`
  line `[the Commissioner, or the order is received by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner, as the case may be, under section 22 or section 23] shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall not apply to the assessment or reassessment made`
  line `in consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in an order under section 21,`
  line `section 22, section 23 ^2`
  line `[or any order of the National Tax Tribunal or of a High Court] or Supreme Court`
  line `in a proceeding by way of reference or appeal under this Act or any order of any court in a proceeding`
  line `otherwise than by way of an appeal or reference under this Act and such assessment or reassessment may,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), be completed at any time.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section, the period`
  line `during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any court shall be`
  line excluded.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 74, ibid., for "the Commissioner, or, as the case may be, the order under section 22 or section 23 is received by the`
  line `Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule, for "or any order of a High Court" (w.e.f. 28-12-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (33238)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Interest on delayed payment of expenditure-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 22, for "one and one-fourth per cent." (w.e.f. 8-9-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33238&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every person responsible for collecting`
  line `expenditure-tax and paying it to the credit of the Central Government in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 7, who fails to credit the tax to the account of the Central Government within the period specified`
  line `in that section, shall pay simple interest at the rate of ^1`
  line `[one per cent.] for every month or part of a month`
  line `by which such crediting of tax is delayed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (33239)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Penalty for failure to collect or pay expenditure-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 117, for section 15 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33239&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[15. Penalty for failure to collect or pay expenditure-tax.--Any person responsible for collecting`
  line `expenditure-tax in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 7,`
  line who--
  line
  line `(a) fails to collect such tax; or`
  line
  line `(b) having collected the tax, fails to pay such tax to the credit of the Central Government in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3) of that section,`
  line
  line `shall pay,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case referred to in clause (a), in addition to paying tax in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (4) of that section, by way of penalty, a sum equal to the amount of tax`
  line `that he failed to collect; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case referred to in clause (b), in addition to paying interest in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 14, by way of penalty, a sum which shall not be less than one hundred rupees`
  line `but which may extend to two hundred rupees for every day during which the failure continues, so,`
  line `however, that the penalty under this clause shall not exceed the amount of tax that he failed to pay.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (33240)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish prescribed return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33240&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If a person fails to furnish in due time the`
  line `return which he is required to furnish under sub-section (1) of section 8 or by notice given under`
  line `sub-section (2) of that section, he shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum which shall not be less than one`
  line `hundred rupees, but which may extend to two hundred rupees for every day during which the failure`
  line continues.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (33241)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Penalty for concealment of chargeable expenditure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33241&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `If the ^1`
  line `[Assesing Officer] or the ^2`
  line [Chief
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] (Appeals) in the course of any proceedings under this Act is satisfied`
  line `that any person has concealed particulars of chargeable expenditure or has furnished inaccurate`
  line `particulars of such chargeable expenditure, he may direct that such person shall pay by way of penalty, in`
  line `addition to any expenditure-tax payable by him, a sum which shall not be less than, but which`
  line `shall not exceed twice, the amount of tax sought to be evaded by reason of concealment of particulars of`
  line `chargeable expenditure or the furnishing of inaccurate particulars of such chargeable expenditure:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the amount of chargeable expenditure (as determined by the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] on`
  line `assessment) in respect of which particulars have been concealed or inaccurate particulars have been`
  line `furnished exceeds a sum of twenty-five thousand rupees, the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] shall not issue any`
  line `direction for payment by way of penalty without the previous approval of the ^3`
  line `[Additional Commissioner`
  line `or, as the case may be, of the Deputy Commissioner].`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for "Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 59, for "Deputy Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (33242)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33242&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] in the course of any`
  line `proceedings under this Act is satisfied that any person has failed to comply with a notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9, he may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, in addition to`
  line `any tax payable by him, a sum which shall not be less than ten per cent. but which shall not exceed fifty`
  line `per cent. of the amount of the tax, if any, which would have been avoided if the chargeable expenditure`
  line `returned by such person had been accepted as the correct chargeable expenditure.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (33243)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Penalty not to be imposed in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33243&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `provisions of section 15, section 16, section 17 or section 18, no penalty shall be imposable on the`
  line `assessee for any failure referred to in the said provisions if he proves that there was reasonable cause for`
  line `the said failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (33244)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Notice of demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `35. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for “Income-tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33244&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `When any tax, interest, penalty or any other sum is payable under this Act,`
  line `the ^35`
  line `Assessing Officer shall serve upon the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed form,`
  line `specifying the sum so payable and the amount of chargeable expenditure in relation to which such sum is`
  line payable.
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (33245)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Revision of orders by the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33245&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, either of his own`
  line `motion or on application by the assessee for revision, call for the record of a proceeding under this Act`
  line `which has been taken by the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] subordinate to him and may make such enquiry or cause`
  line `such enquiry to be made and, subject to the provisions of this Act, may pass such order thereon as he`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) No order which is prejudicial to the assessee shall be passed under this section unless the assessee`
  line `has been given an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) No order under this section shall be passed by the Commissioner, if an appeal against the notice of`
  line `demand issued by the ^2`
  line `[Assessing Officer] under section 20 is pending before the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals).`
  line
  line `(4) No order under this section shall be passed after the expiry of two years from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order sought to be reviewed has been passed.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(6) On every application by an assessee for revision under this sub-section, made on or after the 1st`
  line `day of October, 1998, an order shall be passed within one year from the end of the financial year in which`
  line `such application is made by the assessee for revision.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this sub-section, the time`
  line `taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be re-heard under the proviso to section 24 and any`
  line `period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court`
  line `shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (6), an order in revision under that sub-section`
  line `may be passed at any time in consequence of or to give effect to any finding or direction contained in an`
  line `order of the Appellate Tribunal, ^4`
  line `[the National Tax Tribunal,] the High Court or the Supreme Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 20-12-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (33246)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appeals to the Commissioner (Appeals).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33246&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person objecting to the amount of`
  line `expenditure-tax for which he is assessed by the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer], or denying his liability to be`
  line `assessed under this Act, or objecting to an order levying penalty under this Act, may appeal to the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals).`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Every appeal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the prescribed manner and`
  line `in respect of appeals filed on or after the 1st day of October, 1998, shall be accompanied by a fee of two`
  line `hundred and fifty rupees.]`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal shall be presented within thirty days of the receipt of the notice of demand relating to`
  line `tax, interest or penalty under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner (Appeals) may admit an appeal after the expiration of the said period`
  line `if he is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall hear and determine the appeal and, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, pass such orders as he thinks fit and such orders may include an order enhancing the assessment`
  line `or penalty.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(4A) In every appeal, the Commissioner (Appeals), where it is possible, may hear and determine`
  line `such appeal within a period of one year from the end of the financial year in which such appeal is filed`
  line `under sub-section (1)].`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing the assessment or penalty shall not be made unless the person`
  line `affected thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure to be adopted in the hearing and determination of the appeals shall, with any`
  line `necessary modification, be in accordance with the procedure applicable in relation to income-tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 84, for sub-section (2) (w.e..f. 1-10-1998).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 99, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (33247)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33247&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any assessee aggrieved by an order passed by a`
  line `Commissioner under section 21, or an order passed by a Commissioner (Appeals) under any provision of`
  line `this Act, may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, if he objects to any order passed by the Commissioner (Appeals) under`
  line `any provision of this Act, direct the ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against the`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be filed within sixty days of the date`
  line `on which the order sought to be appealed against is communicated to the assessee or to the`
  line `Commissioner, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The ^1`
  line `[Assessing Officer] or the assessee, as the case may be, on receipt of a notice that an appeal`
  line `against the order of the Commissioner (Appeals) has been preferred under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) by the other party may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order`
  line `or any part thereof, within thirty days of the receipt of the notice, file a memorandum of cross-objections,`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner, against any part of the order of the Commissioner (Appeals), and such`
  line `memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within the`
  line `time specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of`
  line `cross-objections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), if`
  line `it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(6) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall, except in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section (2) or a`
  line `memorandum of cross-objections referred to in sub-section (4), be accompanied by ^2`
  line `[a fee of one`
  line `thousand rupees in the case of appeals filed on or after the 1st day of October, 1998.]`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of this Act, in hearing and making an order on any appeal under this`
  line `section, the Appellate Tribunal shall exercise the same powers and follow the same procedure as it`
  line `exercises and follows in hearing and making an order on any appeal under the Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Income-tax Officer" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 85, for "a fee of two hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (33248)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Application of provisions of Income-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33248&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the following sections and`
  line `Schedules of the Income-tax Act and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules, 1962, as in force`
  line `from time to time, shall apply with necessary modifications as if the said provisions and the rules referred`
  line `to expenditure-tax instead of to income-tax:--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[2(44), 118, 120, 129, 131 to 136 (both inclusive)] 138, ^2`
  line `[139A, 140, 144A, 145], 159 to 163 (both`
  line `inclusive), 166, 167, 170, 171, 173 to 179 (both inclusive), 187, 188, ^3`
  line `[188A] 189, 220 to 227 (both`
  line `inclusive), 229, ^4`
  line `*** 232, 237 to 245 (both inclusive), 254 to 262 (both inclusive), 265, 266, 268, 269,`
  line `278B, 278C, 278D, 278E, ^3`
  line `[279B], 281, 281B, 282, 283, 284, 287, 288, 288A, 288B, 289 to 293 (both`
  line `inclusive), the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that references in the said provisions and rules to the "assessee" shall be construed as`
  line `references to an assessee as defined in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 75, for "2(43B) and (44), 118,125,125A,128 to 136 (both inclusive )" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 118, for "140, 144A" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 118, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `4. The figures "231," omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 75 (w.e.f 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (33249)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Wilful attempt to evade tax, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33249&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `If a person wilfuly attempts in any manner whatsoever to`
  line `evade collection or payment of any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or impossible under this Act, or to`
  line `understate the aggregate of the chargeable expenditure, he shall, without prejudice to any penalty that`
  line `may be imposable on him under any other provision of this Act, be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but which may extend to seven years`
  line `and with fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a wilful attempt to evade collection or payment of any`
  line `tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act shall include a case where any person--`
  line
  line `(i) has in his possession or control any books of account or other documents (being books of`
  line `account or other documents relevant to any proceeding under this Act) containing a false entry or`
  line `statement; or`
  line
  line `(ii) makes or causes to be made any false entry or statement in such books of account or other`
  line `documents; or`
  line
  line `(iii) wilfully omits or causes to be omitted any relevant entry or statement in such books of`
  line `account or other documents; or`
  line
  line `(iv) causes any other circumstances to exist which will have the effect of enabling such person to`
  line `evade collection or payment of any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (33250)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Failure to furnish prescribed returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33250&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `If a person fails to furnish in due time the return which`
  line `he is required to furnish under sub-section (1) of section 8 or by a notice given under sub-section (2) of`
  line `that section, he shall, without prejudice to any penalty that may be imposable on him under any other`
  line `provision of this Act, be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `three months but which may extend to seven years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (33251)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `False statement in verification, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33251&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If a person makes a statement in any verification under`
  line `this Act or any rule made thereunder, or delivers an account or statement which is false, and which he`
  line `either knows or believes to be false, or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but which may extend to seven years`
  line `and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (33252)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Abetment of false return, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33252&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If a person abets or induces in any manner another person to`
  line `make and deliver an account or a statement or declaration relating to any chargeable expenditure which is`
  line `false and which he either knows to be false or does not believe to be true or to commit an offence under`
  line `section 25, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `three months but which may extend to seven years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (33253)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Certain offences to be non-cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33253&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence punishable under section 25 or section 26 or section 27`
  line `or section 28 shall be deemed to be non-cognizable within the meaning of that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (33254)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Institution of proceedings and composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 72, for "Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33254&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be proceeded`
  line `against for any offence under section 25 or section 26 or section 27 or section 28, except with the`
  line `previous sanction of the ^1`
  line `[Chief Commissioner or Commissioner:]`
  line
  line `Provided that no such sanction shall be required where the complainant before the court is a`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals).`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1`
  line `[Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] may, either before or after the institution of`
  line `proceedings, compound any offence punishable under section 25 or section 26 or section 27 or section 28.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (33255)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33255&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, subject to the control of the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the room charges may be determined under ^1`
  line `[sub-clause (a) of clause (1)`
  line `of section 3] in cases where composite charges are payable in respect of residential accommodation`
  line `and food;`
  line
  line `(b) the cases and the circumstances in which payments made in Indian, currency by conversion of`
  line `foreign exchange into Indian currency shall be deemed to have been made in foreign exchange for the`
  line `purposes of clause (a) of the Explanation to ^2`
  line `[clause (1) of section 5.]`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which returns under section 8 may be furnished, the manner in which they may be`
  line `verified and the other particulars which a form may contain;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which a notice of demand may be served on the assessee under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which appeals under section 22 or under sub-section (6) of section 23 may be filed`
  line `and the manner in which they may be verified;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which a memorandum of cross-objections under sub-section (4) of section 23`
  line `may be verified;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which by this Act is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall on the first occasion of the exercise`
  line `thereof include the power to give retrospective effect to the rules or any of them from a date not earlier`
  line `than the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause every rule made under this section to be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 119, for "sub-section (2) of section 3" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991. s. 119, for "section 5" (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (33256)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33256&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (33257)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073&sectionId=33257&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00016_198735_1517807320073
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `[Consequential amendments.]--Rep. by Repealing and Amending Act, 2001 (30 of 2001),`
  line `s. 2 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
